hawaii_total_expenses <- read_csv("Expenses_All_Sports_and_Men's_Women's_and_Coed_Teams_2003_2004_2005_2006_2007_2008_2009_2010_2011_2012_2013_2014_2015_2016_2017_2018.csv") %>%
  rename(Year = "Survey Year") %>%
  rename(Women_Expenses = "Total Women's Team Expenses") %>%
  rename(Men_Expenses = "Total Men's Team Expenses") %>%
  rename(College = "Institution Name") %>%
  select(Year, College, Women_Expenses, Men_Expenses) %>%
  pivot_longer(c("Women_Expenses", "Men_Expenses"), names_to = "Expense_by_Gender", values_to = "Expenses")

# Data object including information on the total expenses going towards the men's and the women's athletic programs at UH from 2003-2018.

diff_men_and_women <- read_csv("Expenses_All_Sports_and_Men's_Women's_and_Coed_Teams_2003_2004_2005_2006_2007_2008_2009_2010_2011_2012_2013_2014_2015_2016_2017_2018.csv") %>%
  rename(Year = "Survey Year") %>%
  rename(Women_Expenses = "Total Women's Team Expenses") %>%
  rename(Men_Expenses = "Total Men's Team Expenses") %>%
  rename(College = "Institution Name") %>%
  select(Year, College, Women_Expenses, Men_Expenses) %>%
  mutate(difference_expenses = Men_Expenses - Women_Expenses)
## Rows: 16 Columns: 168 Column specification

# Data object including information on the difference between the men's and women's expenses at UH from 2003-2018.

mean(diff_men_and_women$difference_expenses)

# Function to calculate the average difference between the men's and women's expenses.

options(scipen = 1000000)

# To add the commas in the ggplot for large numbers

hawaii_total_expenses$Expense_by_Gender = factor(hawaii_total_expenses$Expense_by_Gender, c("Women_Expenses", "Men_Expenses"))

colors <- c("#FF69B4", "dodgerblue")

# Assigning the color pink to denote the women's expenses and the color blue to denote the men's expenses.

ggplot(data = hawaii_total_expenses, mapping = aes(x = Year, y = Expenses, fill = Expense_by_Gender))+
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = position_dodge())+
  labs(title = "Expenses for UH Manoa Women's and Men's Sports from 2003-2018", caption = "Source: U.S. Department of Education Equity in Athletics Data Analysis")+
  xlab("Year")+
  ylab("Expenses")+
  scale_y_continuous(labels = comma)+
  scale_fill_manual(values = colors)

# Bar Plot that shows the expenses for UH Men's and Women's sports from 2003-2018, side-by-side.

ggplot(data = diff_men_and_women, mapping = aes(x = Year, y = difference_expenses))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_line()+
  labs(title = "Difference in Expenses for UH Manoa Women's and Men's Sports from\n 2003-2018", caption = "Source: U.S. Department of Education Equity in Athletics Data Analysis")+
  xlab("Year")+
  ylab("Difference in Expenses")+
  scale_y_continuous(labels = comma)

# Scatter/Line Plot that shows the difference between the men's and women's expenses at UH from 2013-2018.

summary(lm(difference_expenses ~ Year, data = diff_men_and_women))

numberathlete <- read_csv("Athletics_Participation_All_Sports_2003_2018.csv") %>%
  rename(Year = "Survey Year") %>%
  rename(Women_Aid = "Unduplicated Count Women's Participation") %>%
  rename(Men_Aid = "Unduplicated Count Men's Participation") %>%
  rename(College = "Institution Name") %>%
  select(Year, College, Women_Aid, Men_Aid) %>%
  pivot_longer(c("Women_Aid", "Men_Aid"), names_to = "Aid_by_Gender", values_to = "Number_of_Participants")

# Data object including the number of athletes competing in men's sports and women's sports at UH from 2003-2018.  Also, I assigned the names Women_Aid and Men_Aid instead of women's and men's participation because I knew I wanted to join this with the athlete_student_aid data set.

athlete_student_aid <- read_csv("Athletically_Related_Student_Aid_2003_2018.csv") %>%
  rename(Year = "Survey Year") %>%
  rename(Women_Aid = "Women's Team Athletic Student Aid") %>%
  rename(Men_Aid = "Men's Team Athletic Student Aid") %>%
  rename(College = "Institution Name") %>%
  select(Year, College, Women_Aid, Men_Aid) %>%
  pivot_longer(c("Women_Aid", "Men_Aid"), names_to = "Aid_by_Gender", values_to = "Amount_Of_Aid")
## Rows: 16 Columns: 14 Column specification 
## Delimiter: ","
## chr (4): Institution Name, State CD, Classification Name, Sanction Name
## dbl (9): Survey Year, UNITID, Sanction Code, Male Undergraduates, Female Und...
## lgl (1): Classification Other
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
# Data object including the information for the student aid offered to the male and female athletes at UH from 2003-2018.

athlete_student_aid[3, "College"] <- "University of Hawaii at Manoa"

athlete_student_aid[4, "College"] <- "University of Hawaii at Manoa"

# There was an inconsistency in the data set (University of Hawaii at Manoa is capitalized in both of these rows), so I fixed it accordingly.

aid_per_athlete <- left_join(athlete_student_aid, numberathlete, by = c("College", "Year", "Aid_by_Gender")) %>%
  mutate(Aid_Per_Participant = Amount_Of_Aid / Number_of_Participants)

# Joined the athlete_student_aid and numberathlete data objects to form this data object.  This object contains the student aid offered per athlete by taking the total amount of student aid and dividing it by the number of athletes.

aid_per_athlete$Aid_by_Gender = factor(aid_per_athlete$Aid_by_Gender, c("Women_Aid", "Men_Aid"))

colors <- c("#FF69B4", "dodgerblue")

# Assigning the color pink to denote the student aid per female athlete and the color blue to denote the student aid per male athlete.

ggplot(data = aid_per_athlete, aes(x = Year, y = Aid_Per_Participant, fill = Aid_by_Gender))+
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = position_dodge())+
  labs(title = "Student Aid Per Athlete at UH Manoa from 2003-2018", caption = "Source: U.S. Department of Education Equity in Athletics Data Analysis")+
  xlab("Year")+
  ylab("Aid Per Athlete")+
  scale_y_continuous(labels = comma)+
  scale_fill_manual(values = colors)

# Bar Plot comparing the amount of student aid offered per female athlete and the amount of student aid offered per male athlete at UH Manoa from 2003-2018, side-by-side

aid_difference <- aid_per_athlete %>%
  select(Year, College, Aid_by_Gender, Aid_Per_Participant) %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = "Aid_by_Gender", values_from = "Aid_Per_Participant") %>%
  mutate(difference_men_women_aid = Men_Aid - Women_Aid)

# Data object including information on the difference in student aid per athlete between male athletes and female athletes at UH from 2003-2018.

mean(aid_difference$difference_men_women_aid)
## [1] 1053.7
# Computing the average difference in student aid per athlete between male athletes and females athletes.

ggplot(data = aid_difference, aes(x = Year, y = difference_men_women_aid))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_line()+
  labs(title = "Difference in Men's and Women's Student Aid per Athlete at UH from \n2003-2018", caption = "Source: U.S. Department of Education Equity in Athletics Data Analysis")+
  xlab("Year")+
  ylab("Difference in Aid per Athlete")+
  scale_y_continuous(labels = comma)

# Scatter/Line Plot that shows the difference in student aid per athlete between male athletes and female athletes at UH from 2003-2018.

summary(lm(difference_men_women_aid ~ Year, data = aid_difference))

# Computing the average difference in revenue generated between men's and women's sports at UH.

women_revenue_expenses <- hawaii_revenue %>%
  filter(Gender == "Women_Revenue") %>%
  left_join(hawaii_total_expenses, by = c("Year", "College")) %>%
  filter(Expense_by_Gender == "Women_Expenses") %>%
  select(Year, College, Revenue, Expenses) %>%
  mutate(profit_generated = Revenue - Expenses)

# Data Object including information on the expenses, revenue, and profit generated by the women's sports at UH from 2003-2018.

ggplot(data = women_revenue_expenses, aes(x = Year, y = profit_generated))+
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "#FF69B4")+
  labs(title = "Profit Made by UH Women's Sports from 2003-2018", caption = "Source: U.S. Department of Education Equity in Athletics Data Analysis")+
  xlab("Year")+
  ylab("Amount of Profit")+
  scale_y_continuous(labels = comma)

# Bar Plot comparing the amount of profit generated by UH women's sports from 2003-2018.

mean(women_revenue_expenses$profit_generated)
## [1] -2062988
# Computing the average amount of profit generated by UH Women's sports.

men_revenue_expenses <- hawaii_revenue %>%
  filter(Gender == "Men_Revenue") %>%
  left_join(hawaii_total_expenses, by = c("Year", "College")) %>%
  filter(Expense_by_Gender == "Men_Expenses") %>%
  select(Year, College, Revenue, Expenses) %>%
  mutate(profit_generated = Revenue - Expenses)

# Data Object including information on the expenses, revenue, and profit generated by the men's sports at UH from 2003-2018.

ggplot(data = men_revenue_expenses, aes(x = Year, y = profit_generated))+
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", fill = "dodgerblue")+

  xlab("Year")+

  scale_y_continuous(labels = comma)
